Quote: The handpieces of these earlier machines, resembling somewhat those of modern barbers, caused much dissatisfaction. Through overheating and blistering the shearer's hand they were labelled `Hot Boxes', `Smokers' and similar uncomplimentary terms. <i>Ibid.</i> facing 144 [caption] The `smoker', an 1886 Bergen narrow-gear handpiece.
